HEADWORD: Murage
<hw>Mu"rage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>murer</ets> to wall, fr. <ets>mur</ets> wall, L. <ets>murus</ets>.
See <er>Mure</er> a wall.]</ety> <def>A tax or toll paid for building or
repairing the walls of a fortified town.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

